LISBON, July 4 (Reuters) - Following are some of the main stories in Portuguese newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

* President's council calls for post-Troika political consensus (Jornal de Noticias) * Brazil's Oi to decide whether to renew debt issued by Grupo Espirito Santo to Portugal Telecom (Publico) * Angolans prepare to take control of Angolan unit of Banco Espirito Santo (Negocios) * Rights for share offering in bank Millennium bcp <BCP.LS> debut on bourse after rise of over 30 percent (Negocios)